# Unarmed feats
One-Inch Punch					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Unarmed Strike		PRETOTALAB:6	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Flurry of Blows,Brawler ~ Brawler's Flurry						DESC:You combine the force of multiple blows into a single strike to potentially send a foe flying.																												SOURCEPAGE:p.7			BENEFIT:When making a full attack against a corporeal foe, you can forgo multiple attacks to make one unarmed strike at your highest base attack bonus. For each attack you forgo, you can add half your Strength modifier (minimum +0) to your damage roll. If you hit with this attack, you can attempt a bull rush combat maneuver check as a free action, substituting your attack roll result for the combat maneuver check result and adding a bonus equal to half your Strength modifier for each attack you forgo. This bull rush does not provoke an attack of opportunity, and you do not move as a result of the bull rush.
Supefying Strike				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Unarmed Strike		PRETEXT:Dex 13, Wis 13.			PRETOTALAB:8		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13	PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_WIS,13			DESC:You batter your foes with such disorienting force that they can't exert their full abilities.																												SOURCEPAGE:p.7			BENEFIT:When using this feat, in addition to dealing damage normally, you force a foe damaged by your unarmed attack to attempt a Fortitude save (DC %1). If it fails, it loses its skill ranks and activated feats, such as Power Attack or Stunning Fist, for 1d4 rounds. You must declare you are using this feat before you make your attack roll; if you miss, the target is unaffected and your attempt is wasted. You can try to use Stupefying Strike %2 times per day, but no more than once per round. Constructs, incorporeal creatures, mindless creatures, plants, undead, and creatures immune to critical hits can't be affected by this ability.|10+(TL/2)+WIS|TL/4
Unbalancing Blow				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Unarmed Strike		PRETEXT:Dex 13, Wis 13.			PRETOTALAB:4		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13	PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_WIS,13			DESC:With a forceful strike, you throw your foe off-balance.																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.7			BENEFIT:When using this feat, in addition to dealing damage normally, you force a foe damaged by your unarmed attack to attempt a Reflex saving throw (DC = 10 + half your character level + your Wisdom modifier). A creature that fails this saving throw is flat-footed, and if it is larger than Medium size, it loses any special size modifier to its CMD against effects or combat maneuvers that would move it until its next turn. It is also knocked out of any stance associated with a style feat. You must declare that you are using this feat before you make your attack roll; if your attack roll fails, the target is unaffected and your attempt is wasted. You can attempt to use Unbalancing Blow %2 times per day, but no more than once per round. Creatures immune to tripping are immune to this effect.|10+(TL/2)+WIS|TL/4

