Domino Crash					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Reposition,Whipcrack	PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:6],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,3]	PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13		DESC:You knock your opponents into each other, using one enemy to shove aside another.																															SOURCEPAGE:p.24			BENEFIT:When you successfully reposition an opponent, if you attempt to reposition it into a square already occupied by another creature, you can attempt a combat maneuver check as an immediate action to reposition that creature. You take a â4 penalty on this check. If you are successful, the second creature is pushed 5 feet in the direction of your original target's movement. You can move the secondary target an additional 5 feet for every 5 by which you exceed the secondary target's CMD. The secondary target does not provoke attacks of opportunity because of this movement unless you have the Greater Reposition feat. If you fail your combat maneuver check, the movement of your original target ends in front of the secondary target.
Painful Collision				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Bull Rush,Power Attack			PRETEXT:Str 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_STR,13																DESC:You shove your opponents into each other, causing painful and damaging collisions.																															SOURCEPAGE:p.24			BENEFIT:When you bull rush an enemy into another creature, both creatures take 1d6 points of bludgeoning damage, plus an additional 1d6 points of bludgeoning damage for every 5 feet your original target has moved as a result of your bull rush. For instance, if you successfully bull rush a goblin 10 feet and it then collides with another goblin, both creatures would take 3d6 points of bludgeoning damage.
Reverse Somersault Throw		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Drag,Power Attack			PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:6],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,3]		PRETEXT:Str 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_STR,13				DESC:You drag your opponent off balance, then use his momentum to fling him over your head.																														SOURCEPAGE:p.24			BENEFIT:When you succeed at a drag combat maneuver check, at the end of your movement, you can fall prone to launch your target over your head. If you do, you move the target of your drag combat maneuver into the space adjacent to you that is opposite its position at the end of your movement, and the target falls prone in that square or squares. You can't use this ability to move a creature into a square that is occupied by a solid object or obstacle. If there would not be enough room for the creature in its new position, the ability fails and the creature is not moved.
Smashing Impact					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:4,CATEGORY=FEAT,Crushing Impact,Improved Bull Rush,Improved Unarmed Strike,Power Attack			PRETEXT:Str 15		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_STR,15						DESC:The force of your assault drives your opponents against, and possibly through, solid barriers.																												SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:Whenever you successfully bull rush an enemy and its movement is stopped by a solid object or barrier, you can deal your unarmed strike damage to both the foe and the object or barrier, as long as the enemy is within your threatened area. If you performed your bull rush as part of a charge, you gain a +2 bonus on your damage roll. If the damage is enough to destroy the object or barrier, you can continue to push your target the remaining distance allowed by your bull rush combat maneuver.
Whipcrack						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Reposition		PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:3],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,1]	PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13				DESC:You move an opponent and use his momentum to send him reeling across the battlefield.																														SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:When you successfully reposition an opponent, its movement need not remain within your reach, though once the opponent leaves your reach, its remaining movement must be in a straight line. This movement doesn't provoke attacks of opportunity unless you have the Greater Reposition feat.

# Trip Techniques
Tangled Limbs					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Trip,Weapon Focus	PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13															DESC:You twist your long weapon among your target's legs, knocking your foe off-balance.																														SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:When you attempt a trip combat maneuver check with the chosen weapon, your target doesn't receive a bonus to its CMD against your trip attempt for having more than two legs. In addition to the chosen weapon, a character with the weapon training class feature can use Tangled Limbs with any melee weapon from any fighter weapon group that he has selected with weapon training and that has the reach special quality.																																													STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Weapon Focus]
Titan's Tangle					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:4,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Trip,Tangled Limbs,Weapon Focus	PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13											DESC:Even creatures much bigger than you can lose their balance when you apply the appropriate leverage.																										SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:When you attempt a trip combat maneuver check with the chosen weapon, you can try to trip creatures that are up to two size categories larger than you. If you have the Greater Weapon Focus feat with the chosen weapon, you can attempt to trip creatures up to three size categories larger than you are. In addition to the chosen weapon, a character with the weapon training class feature can use Titan's Tangle with any melee weapon from any fighter weapon group that he has selected with weapon training and that has the reach special quality.													STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Weapon Focus]
Toppling Pileup					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Trip			PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13																DESC:When you trip one opponent, its fall might take the legs out from under another creature.																													SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can attempt a single trip combat maneuver check at your full base attack bonus against a foe within reach. If you succeed, the target is knocked prone as normal and you can attempt an additional trip combat maneuver check (using your full base attack bonus) against a foe that is adjacent to the first target and also within reach. You can attempt only one additional combat maneuver per round with this feat.
Tumbling Upset					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Trip		PRESKILL:1,Acrobatics=7		PRETEXT:Int 13		PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13										DESC:You nimbly dodge beneath your opponent, creating an opportunity to upend your foe.																															SOURCEPAGE:p.25			BENEFIT:When you succeed at an Acrobatics check to move through an enemy's space, you can spend a swift action to attempt a trip combat maneuver check against the opponent. Even if you fail this check by 10 or more, you do not fall prone.

# General Feats
Change of Heart					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General				PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:6],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,6]																																		DESC:At the moment of your victory, you can help your foe to see as you do.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:When your melee attack would reduce an opponent to 0 or fewer hit points or render the opponent unconscious, you can elect to forgo this damage and instead attempt a Diplomacy check to influence the target's attitude. The DC of this check is equal to 20 + the creature's Hit Dice + the creature's Charisma modifier. You gain a bonus equal to half the damage you would have dealt and can use your base attack bonus instead of your ranks in Diplomacy. Unlike with a normal Diplomacy check, you can increase the target's attitude toward you by more than two steps. You can use the benefits of this feat only against enemies who attacked you and whom you did not attack or otherwise provoke first. 
Merciful Takedown				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																																		DESC:You are adept at removing your defeated opponents from the fight while avoiding their deaths.																												SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:When you perform a coup de grace and deal only nonlethal damage, instead of attempting a Fortitude save to avoid death, the target must instead attempt a Fortitude save to avoid falling unconscious for 1 hour. The DC of this save is the same as that of a lethal coup de grace.

# Signature Move Feats
Crippling Thrust				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Weapon Focus		PRETOTALAB:6																															DESC:With one precise stab, you hamper movement.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:As a standard action, make a single attack with your chosen weapon. If the attack hits, the target's movement speed is halved until the start of your next turn. When your base attack bonus reaches +11, the target's movement is so hampered that even a 5-foot step provokes an attack of opportunity. When your base attack bonus reaches +16, the target must also succeed at a Reflex save with a DC equal to 10 + your base attack bonus or become entangled. An entangled creature's movement can be halved only once. You can use this feat's benefits only once per minute.							STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Weapon Focus]
Meteor Swing					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Weapon Focus		PRETOTALAB:6																															DESC:The power of your blow leaves your enemies reeling.																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:As a standard action, make a single attack with your chosen weapon. If the attack hits, the target must succeed at a Reflex save with a DC equal to 10 + your base attack bonus or lose its ability to make attacks of opportunity until the beginning of your next turn. When your base attack bonus reaches +11, you can instead cause the target to lose its Dexterity bonus to AC. When your base attack bonus reaches +16, you can instead cause the target to become flat footed. You can use this feat's benefits only once per minute.																	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Weapon Focus]
Pinpoint Jab					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Unarmed Strike	PRETEXT:Ki Pool or Martial Flexibility class feature	PRETOTALAB:6															DESC:You strikes land exactly where you mean them to.																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:As a full-round action, you can expend 1 ki point or one daily use of martial flexibility to use a limited version of the Targeted Strike deed, targeting either hands or legs with an unarmed attack. A target who succeeds at a Fortitude save (DC %1) can negate the effect. When your base attack bonus reaches +11, you can instead target head or torso, which the target can negate with a Fortitude save. When your BAB reaches +16, you can target two locations; the target must save against each effect separately. A monk can substitute his class level for his base attack bonus for this feat's effects.|10+BAB
Storm of Blades					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Weapon Focus		PRETOTALAB:6																															DESC:Your technique unleashes a dizzying torrent of cuts.																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.26			BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can make a single attack with your chosen weapon while setting up a vortex of cuts that lasts until the beginning of your next turn. Any creature that begins its turn threatened by this weapon takes damage equal to your Strength or Dexterity bonus, whichever is greater. When your base attack bonus reaches +11, you also add your base weapon damage. When your base attack bonus reaches +16, you gain the distraction universal monster rule for this damage, but a creature that fails its save is only sickened. You can use this feat's benefits only once per minute.	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Weapon Focus]

